### Create order for user 1
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "totalAmount": 99.99
}

###

### Create another order for user 1
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "totalAmount": 49.50
}

###

### Get all orders for user 1
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders

###

### Get specific order
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/1

###

### Update order status
PATCH http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/1/status?status=CONFIRMED

###

### Try wrong user id (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/999/orders/1

###

### Delete order
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/2



### Add items to order 1 (create user + order first)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/1/items
Content-Type: application/json

{ "productId": 1, "quantity": 2 }

###

### Add second product to same order
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/1/items
Content-Type: application/json

{ "productId": 2, "quantity": 3 }

###

### Add same product again — quantity should increase
POST http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/1/items
Content-Type: application/json

{ "productId": 1, "quantity": 1 }

###

### Get all items in order
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/1/items

###

### Get order — check totalAmount updated
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/1

### Create test products (run multiple times with different names)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{ "name": "Key", "description": "Key chain holder",
  "price": 79.99, "stockQuantity": 100 }

###

### Get first page — default size 10, sorted by createdAt desc
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products

###

### Get page 0, size 2, sorted by price ascending
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products?page=0&size=2&sort=price,asc

###

### Get page 1, size 2 (second page)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products?page=1&size=2&sort=price,asc

###

### Search by name with pagination
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products?name=key&page=0&size=5

###

### Try invalid sort field (expect 400)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products?sort=description,asc

###

### Paginated orders for user 1
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/paged?page=0&size=3

###

### Try size above max (should be capped at 100)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products?size=999

### User order summaries (Query 10)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/analytics/users/order-summary

###

### Top spenders above £50 (Query 11)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/analytics/users/top-spenders?minSpend=50

###

### Total spent by user 1 (Query 3)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/analytics/users/1/total-spent

###

### Low stock products (threshold 100) (Query 7)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/analytics/products/low-stock?threshold=100

###

### Who purchased product 1? (Query 12 — 3 entity join)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/analytics/products/1/purchasers

###

### Orders in date range (Query 1)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/search/date-range?from=2026-01-01T00:00:00&to=2026-12-31T23:59:59

###

### Orders above amount (Query 2)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/search/min-amount?minAmount=50

###

### Filtered + paginated orders (Query 5)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/filtered?status=PENDING&page=0&size=5

###

### Filtered with no status filter (null passes through)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/1/orders/filtered?page=0&size=5

###

### Full text product search (Query 8)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products?name=lap


### Register a new user
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### Register second user (will be ADMIN later)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Admin User",
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "adminpass123"
}

###

### Try duplicate registration (expect 409)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Again",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### Login
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### Wrong password (expect 401)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

###

### Refresh token — paste refreshToken from login response
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "paste-your-refresh-token-here"
}

###

### Logout
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "paste-your-refresh-token-here"
}

###

### Try refresh after logout (expect 401)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "paste-your-refresh-token-here"
}

