### ── COOKIE MODE TESTS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Cookie register — response body has user, no tokens
### Check response headers for Set-Cookie
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/cookie/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bob",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### Cookie login — sets cookies, no tokens in body
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/cookie/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### Access protected route WITH cookie (IntelliJ HTTP client sends cookies automatically)
### After cookie login above, this should work without Authorization header
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/me

###

### Cookie refresh — no body, reads cookie automatically
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/cookie/refresh

###

### Cookie logout — clears cookies
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/cookie/logout

###

### After cookie logout — access should fail (expect 401)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/me